<HEADLINE>  Griffin Sets U.S. Record in 200M </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Rohsaan Griffin cracked the American indoor  
record in the 200 meters, winning in 20.32 seconds in the USA 
Indoor Track and Field Championships at the Georgia Dome Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Griffin's time broke the mark of 20.40 shared by 1997 world  
indoor champion Kevin Little and Jeff Williams. It fell far short 
of the world record of 19.92 held by Frankie Fredericks of Namibia. 
</P>
<P>
	Little finished second Saturday in 20.41.  
</P>
