<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Banshee Breeze Wins Rampert Debut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HALLANDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Banshee Breeze, the Eclipse Award winner  
as last year's top 3-year-old filly, made her 4-year-old debut a 
successful one Sunday with a 5 1/2-length victory in the $200,000 
Rampart Handicap at Gulfstream Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Jerry Bailey, Banshee Breeze put away Glitter Woman in  
the final furlong to outrun the five-horse field in a time of 1:42 
4-5 over the 1 1-16 miles. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze, the 3-5 favorite, returned $3.20, $2.10 and  
$2.10 for her seventh career victory. Glitter Woman paid $2.20 and 
$2.10, and Timely Broad finished another four lengths back and paid 
$2.10 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight horses were entered, but two early scratches reduced the  
field to six. That included Harpia, who had won five straight since 
returning to the United States from France but came down Sunday 
with a sinus infection. 
</P>
<P>
	Angel of a Mom also had to be scratched when she ran off during  
warmups. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze, carrying the top weight of 122 pounds, was  
making her first start since losing by a nose to Escena in the 
Breeders' Cup Distaff last November. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze raced only once as a 2-year-old, finishing  
seventh. But she finished in the money in all 10 starts last year, 
winning six times with two second-place finishes and two thirds. 
Sunday's win increased her career earnings to $1,545,980. 
</P>
<P>
	The daughter of former Kentucky Derby winner Unbridled ran  
second to Glitter Woman after a half-mile, then moved alongside the 
leader at the quarter pole and asserted her authority down the 
stretch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
