<HEADLINE> A Look at the Ford 2000 Excurion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	2000 FORD EXCURSION   	
</P>
<P>
	Vehicle type: Sport utility vehicle, built on medium-duty truck  
chassis. 
</P>
<P>
	Manufacturer: Ford Motor Co.  
</P>
<P>
	Assembly: Louisville, Ky.  
</P>
<P>
	On sale: Oct. 1.  
</P>
<P>
	Superlatives: Longest, widest, heaviest SUV on the market.  
</P>
<P>
	Engines: 5.4-liter V8; optional 6.8-liter V10; optional  
7.3-liter V8 diesel. 
</P>
<P>
	Transmission: Four-speed automatic; two- or four-wheel drive.  
</P>
<P>
	Seats: Eight or nine in three rows, depending on trim package.  
</P>
<P>
	Cargo space: 48.6 cubic feet behind the third-row seats; 165  
cubic feet with second row folded and third row removed. 
</P>
<P>
	Fuel capacity: 44 gallons.  
</P>
<P>
	Fuel economy: Estimated at 10-18 mpg, depending on engine.  
</P>
<P>
	Towing capacity: 5 tons.  
</P>
<P>
	Safety: Dual front air bags, below-bumper beam to prevent  
overriding a car in head-on crash. 
</P>
<P>
	Cupholders: Up to 10, depending on trim package.  
</P>
<P>
	Power outlets: Five.  
</P>
<P>
	Recyclability: More than 85 percent of materials recyclable when  
vehicle is scrapped. 



</P>
</TEXT>
