<HEADLINE> Naehring Accepts Reds Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Former Boston Red Sox infielder Tim Naehring  
accepted a minor league contract with the Cincinnati Reds on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	He was to report to spring training in Sarasota, Fla., on Monday  
to continue rehabilitation of his injured right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Naehring, 32, hasn't played since June 1997 because of the  
injury. In eight seasons with Boston, he appeared in 547 games and 
batted .282 with 49 home runs and 260 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	While continuing rehab, Naehring also will be a special  
assistant to the general manager, working in player development and 
scouting. 
