<HEADLINE> Desert Hero Wins San Rafael Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Desert Hero staged a furious rally to  
defeat Prime Timber by a head Sunday to win the $200,000 San Rafael 
Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
	Desert Hero, the son of 1993 Kentucky Derby champion Sea Hero,  
started the one-mile race in fourth and jockey Corey Nakatani bided 
his time until the sixth furlong. 
</P>
<P>
	Prime Timber took the lead in the midstretch, but Desert Hero  
closed in at the eighth pole. 
</P>
<P>
	Desert Hero finished the race in 1:36 2/5 to pay $22.80, $9, and  
$6.40. It was the second win for the yearling, whose earnings now 
total $147,000. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was pretty tight in the stretch,'' Nakatani said. ``The  
hole closed up, but I just sat on him, moved the outside, and he 
put in a big kick like I thought he would.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Prime Timber, ridden by Gary Stevens, paid $3.60 and $3.  
</P>
<P>
	Capsized came in third to pay $5.60.  
</P>
