<HEADLINE> Man Arrested in Fatal Mass. Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LYNN, Mass. (AP) -- The mother of a man police said threatened  
his ex-girlfriend's building with arson has been arrested in 
connection with a fire that killed five people there. 
</P>
<P>
	Catherine Hilton, 52, was scheduled to be arraigned Monday on  
murder and arson charges. She was arrested Saturday. Her son is no 
longer a suspect in the case, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We all felt we had probable cause to make her arrest and  
charge her with the crime,'' prosecutor Kevin Burke said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities last week had arrested the son, 22-year-old Charles  
Loayza, and charged him with violating a restraining order after he 
threatened to burn the building where his ex-girlfriend, Krystina 
Sutherland, lived. He still faces that charge. 
</P>
<P>
	Burke said Hilton was aware of her son's volatile relationship  
with Sutherland. 
</P>
<P>
	``The nature of the relationship (between Loayza and Sutherland)  
was the basic fundamental cause or part of the motive for the 
fire,'' Burke said. 
</P>
