<HEADLINE> Evangelist Roberts Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Evangelist Oral Roberts was  
hospitalized in stable condition Sunday after suffering a mild 
heart attack two weeks ago, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Roberts, 81, underwent an angioplasty procedure at Hoag Memorial  
Hospital Presbyterian to reopen a primary artery in his heart -- the 
same artery that caused heart problems six years ago, hospital 
spokeswoman Debra Legan said. 
</P>
<P>
	The angioplasty was performed without any complications, she  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Oral is now recuperating. We hope he will be up and going  
soon,'' a statement released by the family said. 
</P>
<P>
	Roberts founded the Oral Roberts University in Tulsa, Okla., and  
retired as its president in 1993. His son, Richard, is now 
president of the university, but Roberts still serves as chancellor 
and travels around the country on speaking engagements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
