<HEADLINE> Hasbro Creates Bob Hope G.I. Doll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bob Hope, who has received numerous accolades  
for entertaining U.S. troops, is getting another honor: a G.I. doll 
created in his likeness. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hollywood Hero'' has been designed to pay homage to the  
95-year-old comedian, who spent a half-century entertaining U.S. 
troops around the world. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've heard how much he likes it,'' Jon Fitch, associate  
marketing manager of Hasbro, told the March 6 edition of TV Guide. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hope Enterprises was involved in all of it, right down to the  
scoop on the nose,'' Fitch said. ``They even asked us to make it 
more prominent than we originally had it.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
