<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Barkley Returns; Denigrates Lakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Charles Barkley ripped into the Los  
Angeles Lakers on Sunday before returning to action against them 
two weeks to the day after undergoing arthroscopic knee surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm so disgusted by NBC and the L.A. press,'' Barkley told  
reporters an hour before the Houston Rockets and Lakers played 
their nationally televised game at the Forum. ``You guys make me 
sick. I'm sick of NBC showing the Lakers every week and saying how 
good they are. They're a glamour team. 
</P>
<P>
	``You all picked them to win the championship. Now, they're  
struggling. Now, they bring in Dennis Rodman and they're going to 
win the championship again. They've got a lot of talent. They're 
8-6, aren't they?'' 
</P>
<P>
	That was before the game. Rick Fox scored 15 of his 21 points in  
the first 6:55 of the fourth quarter and Rodman provided a spark 
with 10 rebounds and defensive energy as the Lakers beat the 
Rockets 106-90 to raise their record to 9-6. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley, who averaged 19.2 points and 17.0 rebounds in five  
games before having surgery to repair a tear of the medial meniscus 
in his left knee, had 14 points and six rebounds in 19 minutes of 
action. He had said beforehand he hoped to play 30 minutes but 
would settle for 25. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley said prior to the game he thought the best teams in the  
Western Conference right now are defending conference champion Utah 
and Portland. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're right there,'' he said. ``I like our team a lot. We're  
going to be good. We've got a lot of good pieces. We were playing 
really well before I got hurt. We just have to play like we were 
playing. 
</P>
<P>
	``Right now, I see (the Western Conference) as a three-team race  
-- Portland, Utah and us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When asked if he ranked the Lakers fourth in the West, he smiled  
and said, ``I don't rank 'em. They don't get anything for coming in 
fourth.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley, who turned 36 on Feb. 20, brought career averages of  
22.5 points and 11.7 rebounds into the season. He has never played 
on a championship team. 
</P>
<P>
	When asked about new teammate Scottie Pippen, who played on six  
championship teams with the Chicago Bulls and Michael Jordan, 
Barkley said, ``He's not the guy (with the Rockets) right now. I'm 
the guy when I'm healthy. He was in Michael's shadow because he was 
supposed to be. Somebody always has to be the main guy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	About returning to action two weeks after undergoing surgery,  
Barkley said, ``I worked hard on my rahab. The main reason I came 
back, my team needs me. We struggled without me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockets (8-6) were 4-1 before Barkley underwent surgery and  
were 4-4 without him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
